Issue 1: Missing Dependency Array (CRITICAL)
Current Problematic Code (Line 93-101): 
useEffect(()=>{
   // Match URLs like /notes/noteId
   const match = pathname.match(/^\/notes\/([^\/\?]+)/);
   if (match && match[1]) {
     const noteId = match[1];
     previousNoteIdRef.current = noteId;
   } else {
    previousNoteIdRef.current = null;
   }
},[]) // âŒ EMPTY dependency array! 
Problems:
Dead code - This was the correct implementation but is commented out
Missing functionality - setSelectedNoteId is never called, so selectedNoteId state is never updated
UI inconsistency - Sidebar won't highlight the currently selected note
âœ… Corrected Phase 1 Solutions 
useEffect(() => {
  // Match URLs like /notes/noteId
  const match = pathname.match(/^\/notes\/([^\/\?]+)/);
  if (match && match[1]) {
    const noteId = match[1];
    setSelectedNoteId(noteId); // âœ… Restore this functionality
    previousNoteIdRef.current = noteId;
  } else {
    setSelectedNoteId(null); // âœ… Restore this functionality
    previousNoteIdRef.current = null;
  }
}, [pathname]); // âœ… Add pathname dependency 
useEffect(() => {
  try {
    // Match URLs like /notes/noteId
    const match = pathname.match(/^\/notes\/([^\/\?]+)/);
    if (match && match[1]) {
      const noteId = match[1];
      setSelectedNoteId(noteId);
      previousNoteIdRef.current = noteId;
    } else {
      setSelectedNoteId(null);
      previousNoteIdRef.current = null;
    }
  } catch (error) {
    console.error("Error parsing note ID from pathname:", error);
    setSelectedNoteId(null);
    previousNoteIdRef.current = null;
  }
}, [pathname]);--{Fix 3: Add Error Boundary} What's Actually Wrong:
Missing dependency causing the effect to never run
Commented functionality breaking note selection
No error handling for malformed URLs
Priority: HIGH - This breaks core navigation functionality and note selection in the sidebar.
